&lt;h2 id=&#34;pigsty-enterprise&#34;&gt;Pigsty Enterprise&lt;/h2&gt;


&lt;div class=&#34;alert alert-primary&#34; role=&#34;alert&#34;&gt;
&lt;h4 class=&#34;alert-heading&#34;&gt;$15,000 / node·year, at least 4 nodes with $60,000 / year&lt;/h4&gt;

    

&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Pigsty Enterprise Subscription encompasses all services provided under the Professional Subscription and extends additional premium services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Enterprise subscription offers the most extensive support range for database and operating system versions, including extended support for end-of-life systems such as EL7, U20, D11,
and obsolete database major versions beginning with PG 12. This edition also supports &lt;strong&gt;Arm64&lt;/strong&gt; arch.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Subscribers can replace the native PostgreSQL kernel with &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.itsec.gov.cn/aqkkcp/cpgg/202312/t20231226_162074.html&#34;&gt;PolarDB v2.0&lt;/a&gt; (purchased separately) in Pigsty to meet certain compliance requirements.
And other kernels can also be used instead of the default PostgreSQL kernel.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Enterprise subscription provides enhanced consulting services with a commitment to 24/7 support and a response time SLA of less than one hour.
Additional consulting services include version upgrades, performance bottleneck check, annual architectural assessments, and extension packaging support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Enterprise subscription includes &lt;strong&gt;2&lt;/strong&gt; expert man-days per year, with more available for purchase, addressing more complex and time-consuming issues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pricing for the Enterprise Subscription is set at &lt;strong&gt;$15,000 / node·year&lt;/strong&gt;, starting with &lt;strong&gt;4 nodes&lt;/strong&gt;, and a minimum total cost of &lt;strong&gt;$64,000 / year&lt;/strong&gt;
—— which equivalent to &lt;strong&gt;24 vCPU&lt;/strong&gt; AWS RDS for PostgreSQL.&lt;/p&gt;
