&lt;h3 id=&#34;feature-enhancements&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Feature Enhancements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Compared to the open-source version, Pigsty Pro and Enterprise editions include additional features:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compatibility&lt;/strong&gt;: Run on all mainstream Linux OS distros: EL, Debian, Ubuntu.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Offline Install&lt;/strong&gt;: Use pre-made offline packages for precise OS minor versions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Multi-Version PG&lt;/strong&gt;: Install and run different PostgreSQL versions simultaneously. (13-17)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Replaceable Kernel&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;/docs/kernel/babelfish/&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Babelfish&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Microsoft SQL Server compatibility @ TSQL &amp;amp; TDS wire protocol level.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;/docs/kernel/ivorysql/&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IvorySQL&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Oracle syntax/type/PL compatibility based on PG (EL only).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;/docs/kernel/polardb/&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PolarDB PG&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Open-source Aurora-Flavor cloud database, PolarDB for PostgreSQL.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;/docs/kernel/polardb-o/&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PolarDB O&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Trustworthy, Oracle-compatible kernel meeting China domestic compliance (&lt;strong&gt;Enterprise only&lt;/strong&gt;).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Extension Packaging&lt;/strong&gt;: Ready-to-use installation for 340 PG Extensions on PG 12 - 17 across major OSs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Extra Modules&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;/docs/kernel/supabase/&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Supabase&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Reliable self-hosted, production-level open-source Firebase alternative.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;/docs/minio/&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;MinIO&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Enterprise-level PB object storage setup.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;/docs/pro/duckdb/&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;DuckDB&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Comprehensive support for DuckDB and PostgreSQL + DuckDB OLAP extension plugins.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;/docs/pro/kafka/&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Kafka&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: High-availability Kafka cluster deployment and monitoring.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Kubernetes, VictoriaMetrics &amp;amp; VictoriaLogs (TBD)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ARM Arch Support&lt;/strong&gt;: Support for ARM64 architecture (&lt;strong&gt;Enterprise only&lt;/strong&gt;).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pigsty CLI&lt;/strong&gt; (Beta).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;payment-model&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Payment Model&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pigsty subscriptions are annual. Contracts start on the agreed date. Payments before expiration imply automatic renewal.
Continuous subscriptions are discounted: 5% off the second year, 10% off subsequent years, and 15% off for three-year commitments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Post-subscription, non-renewal results in cessation of updates, tech support, and consulting, though previously installed Pro software remains usable.
Non-renewal gaps do not incur back pay upon re-subscription, but discounts reset.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pigsty&amp;rsquo;s pricing ensures value—immediate access to top-tier DBA database architecture and management practices at a competitive cost
relative to hiring full-time experts or using cloud databases. Reference market prices for comparable enterprise database services:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://instances.vantage.sh/rds/&#34;&gt;AWS RDS for PostgreSQL HA&lt;/a&gt;: $160 – $220 / (vCPU·month), equivalent to &lt;strong&gt;$1920 ~ $2640/year&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;strong&gt;per vCPU&lt;/strong&gt;).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.enterprisedb.com/products/plans-comparison#edbbiganimalcommunity360plan&#34;&gt;EDB PostgreSQL Cloud Database Enterprise&lt;/a&gt;: $183.3 / (vCPU·month), equivalent to &lt;strong&gt;$2200/year&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;strong&gt;per vCPU&lt;/strong&gt;).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.enterprisedb.com/products/plans-comparison#edbbiganimalcommunity360plan&#34;&gt;Fujitsu Enterprise PostgreSQL Kubernetes&lt;/a&gt;: $3200 / (Core·year), equivalent to &lt;strong&gt;$1200/year&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;strong&gt;per vCPU&lt;/strong&gt;).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.oracle.com/a/ocom/docs/corporate/pricing/technology-price-list-070617.pdf&#34;&gt;Oracle Annual Service Fee&lt;/a&gt;: (Enterprise $47,500 + Rac $23,000) * 22% per year, equivalent to &lt;strong&gt;$3878/year&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;strong&gt;per vCPU&lt;/strong&gt;).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fair market rates for respectable database services range from &lt;strong&gt;$1K ~ $4K/year&lt;/strong&gt; per &lt;strong&gt;vCPU&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pigsty&amp;rsquo;s &lt;strong&gt;5K/15K per-node&lt;/strong&gt; pricing on high-end servers just offers unmatched cost efficiency.&lt;/p&gt;
